      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Get your VM readu to use R and RStudion. Follow the instruction on Option 2 for Windows users. <br /></p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Option 2: Using your personal machine <br /></p>

    <p>This option has distinct guides depending on which operating system you use. <br /></p>

    <p><a href="/docs/modules/readings/soft-win/"> Guide for Windows users or students using a VM </a> <br /></p>

    <p><a href="/docs/modules/readings/soft-mac/"> Guide for Mac users </a> <br /></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Option 3: Using RStudio container</p>

    <p>A ‚Äúcontainer‚Äù is a web-based resource pre-configured to run all the software you need, but only that software. RStudio will work and appear just as they would on a typical desktop machine. No installation requires. You just need to set it up.</p>

    <ol>
      <li>Navigate to <a href="https://cmgr.oit.duke.edu/containers">https://cmgr.oit.duke.edu/containers</a> and log in. <br /></li>
      <li>Click on the reserve RStudio button.</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
</ul>

